---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Header from "./components/Header.astro";
---

<MainLayout>
  <div class="mt-16 sm:mt-32">
    <Header
      title="Tools of the Trade"
      subtitle="A peek behind the curtain ‚Äì the stuff that keeps me running (and coding)."
    />
    <div class="mt-16 sm:mt-20">
      <div class="space-y-20">
        <section
          aria-labelledby=":r0R6:"
          class="md:border-l md:border-zinc-100 md:pl-6 md:dark:border-zinc-700/40"
        >
          <div
            class="grid max-w-3xl grid-cols-1 items-baseline gap-y-8 md:grid-cols-4"
          >
            <h2
              id=":r0R6:"
              class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
            >
              Workstation
            </h2><div class="md:col-span-3">
              <ul role="list" class="space-y-16">
                <li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    16‚Äù MacBook Pro, Intel Core i9, 32GB RAM (2019)
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    M1 Macbooks are great but I'm sticking to my good old Intel
                    Mac which still handles heavy workloads without a hitch.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    4k 32‚Äù LG UltraFine Display Ergo
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Bigger the display, bigger the motivation to use it to read
                    your code üòÜ - also the the ergonomic stand that comes with
                    this model ü§å
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Keychron K4 Wireless Mechanical Keyboard
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Mechanical Keyboards are ‚ù§Ô∏è and the satisfying clicks of the
                    normal profile Keychron keyboard is the reason I code most
                    of the time. Fun-fact, I learnt typing with a traditional
                    type-writer which I badly miss now.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Logitech MX Master 3
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    As a power user of VSCode, tmux &amp; the tiles app in the
                    Mac, I rarely need to click stuff on the screen. But when I
                    do, I do it with the most erogonomic MX Master 3.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Monarch Elevate: Height Adjustable Table
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Because, sitting too much while you are thinking about what
                    to name that variable is bad for your health. Always switch
                    between sitting &amp; standing every 1 hour &amp; 15 mins
                    respectively.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Senheisser HD 458BT headphones
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Most trusted headphones for work - taking video calls,
                    watching egghead lessons, listening to podcasts while coding
                    - can't live without this one.
                  </p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section><section
          aria-labelledby=":r0Ra:"
          class="md:border-l md:border-zinc-100 md:pl-6 md:dark:border-zinc-700/40"
        >
          <div
            class="grid max-w-3xl grid-cols-1 items-baseline gap-y-8 md:grid-cols-4"
          >
            <h2
              id=":r0Ra:"
              class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
            >
              Development tools
            </h2><div class="md:col-span-3">
              <ul role="list" class="space-y-16">
                <li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    VSCodium
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    A completely open-source variant of the VSCode with its own
                    marketplace that supports all my vital extensions &amp; a
                    great logo.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Oh My Zsh!
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    I can't use my mac terminal without installing Oh My Zsh
                    &amp; setting up my favorite theme. Who wants to cd into a
                    directory, when you can just type the directory name
                    directly!
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    tmux
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    With large screens comes no reason to open multiple tabs in
                    your terminal - just keep the processes running across the
                    tmux profiles.
                  </p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section><section
          aria-labelledby=":r0Re:"
          class="md:border-l md:border-zinc-100 md:pl-6 md:dark:border-zinc-700/40"
        >
          <div
            class="grid max-w-3xl grid-cols-1 items-baseline gap-y-8 md:grid-cols-4"
          >
            <h2
              id=":r0Re:"
              class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
            >
              Design
            </h2><div class="md:col-span-3">
              <ul role="list" class="space-y-16">
                <li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Figma
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    They say figma is a great design tool, but I use it to build
                    flow charts &amp; stick-figure prototypes of my weekend
                    projects. I love it &amp; I can't think of using another
                    tool to do this.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Excalidraw
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Professional quality scribbling &amp; a very funny logo
                    maker. I'd say this is my preferred design tool.
                  </p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section><section
          aria-labelledby=":r0Ri:"
          class="md:border-l md:border-zinc-100 md:pl-6 md:dark:border-zinc-700/40"
        >
          <div
            class="grid max-w-3xl grid-cols-1 items-baseline gap-y-8 md:grid-cols-4"
          >
            <h2
              id=":r0Ri:"
              class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
            >
              Productivity
            </h2><div class="md:col-span-3">
              <ul role="list" class="space-y-16">
                <li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Tiles
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    By removing the use of mouse to resize &amp; move windows
                    across the screen, I'm 2x more efficient but also 2x less
                    efficient by wasting time deciding which window to place in
                    which section of the screen.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Notion
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Pretty much all my ideas, projects, plans &amp; thoughts
                    about my digital life are recorded in the generous free tier
                    provided the Notion app.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Spark
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Keeping my inbox clean by only reading the messages filtered
                    by this great email app.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Cron
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    They say it's an extremely powerful tool for managing
                    calendars, but I use it because it's event reminders are so
                    much better than the native mac calendar app.
                  </p>
                </li><li class="group relative flex flex-col items-start">
                  <h3
                    class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-100"
                  >
                    Simplenote
                  </h3><p
                    class="relative z-10 mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400"
                  >
                    Replacing the need for paper in my life. Works across all my
                    devices - take a quick note whenever you want &amp; forget
                    about it forever.
                  </p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
